Editors make thousands of changes everyday for various reasons, including fixing spelling mistakes, rephrasing sentences, updating information on controversial topics, and fixing factual mistakes. The work focuses on mining data from the last category. In particular, it looks at sentence edits in Wikipedia where only 1 entity or 1 number is changed.